Package org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.application.ambassador.simulation.perception.index.objects

Class VehicleBoundingBox

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.application.ambassador.simulation.perception.index.objects.VehicleBoundingBox
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, SpatialObjectBoundingBox
public class VehicleBoundingBox extends Object implements SpatialObjectBoundingBox
An object representing a vehicles' 2D bounding box. 
   frontRightCorner----------rightEdge----------backRightCorner
                  |                             |
   Heading <== frontEdge                     backEdge
                  |                             |
    frontLeftCorner----------leftEdge-----------backLeftCorner
All points are in global coordinates.

    • createFromVehicleObject

      public static VehicleBoundingBox createFromVehicleObject(VehicleObject vehicleObject)
      This method is used to generate a VehicleBoundingBox-object given its position, dimensions, and heading. Note: We assume that the position is defined in the middle of the front bumper and the heading is defined relative to this position.
      Parameters:
      vehicleObject - the VehicleObject containing its dimensions and heading
      Returns:
      the build VehicleBoundingBox
